functions.name: TemplateManager_Create_Item_Module
functions.description:
### 	Creates an item that references a specific module
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

This function was added specifically to enable the creation of Store Morph items from inside Module_Install_Store() of a currency, tax, or storeui module, but may
also be used elsewhere when a full Module record is available, to avoid explicitly loading the record from the database.

For a complete description of the issues resolved by calling this function, see http://bugzilla.mivamerchant.com/show_bug.cgi?id=5240

* __@param__ [in] code The code of the newly created Item
* __@param__ [in] module A complete Module record describing the component module which will implement the item

\return		1 on success, 0 on error

functions.name: OrderMinimumsMet
functions.description:
### Determines if the current shopping basket meets the configured minimums for checkout

Examines the contents of the shopping basket in g.Basket to determine if it meets the minimum checkout settings for the store.
Both the minimum quantity of items and the minimum total price are verified.

\return	1 if the basket meets the configured requirements, 0 if it does not

functions.name: DetermineSessionID
functions.description:
### 		Sets up variables identifying the current shopping interface session

This function parses input parameters and cookies to identify and verify a shopping interface session.
The function also calls SetRuntimePaths() to initialize variables dependent on the current site configuration.
Initializing g.Store_Code prior to calling this function will eliminate overhead.

Input cookies are parsed using ParseCookies() and stored in the variable g.Request_Cookies.

\return			The value of g.Session_ID

\sa			SetRuntimePaths ParseCookies

functions.name: UpdateSessionID
functions.description:
### 	Updates URL variables and cookies to reflect changes in session variables
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

This function should be called whenever the value of one of the session variables is changed.

\sa		SetRuntimePaths SetRuntimeCookies

functions.name: SetRuntimePaths
functions.description:
### 	Initializes shopping session specific variables
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

This function examines the current shopping environment, configuration, and session, then initializes variables
required for proper navigation of the store.

functions.name: SetRuntimeCookies
functions.description:
### 	Outputs Set-Cookie headers for appropriate shopping session cookies
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

This function outputs Set-Cookie headers to update or create shopping session cookies.  

When called in response to an HTTP request, the following cookies are updated:
* mm5-[store_code]-basket-id

When called in response to an HTTPS request, the following cookies are updated:
* mm5-[store_code]-customer-session
* mm5-[store_code]-affiliate-session
* mm5-[store_code]-checkout-session

If a session value does not exist for any of the cookies above, that cookie is explicitly cleared by specifying an expiration date one year in the past.

Cookies are contained in the cookie list g.Output_Cookies.

\return		1 if cookies are properly updated, 0 if they were not

\sa SetCookie ClearCookie OutputCookies

functions.name: OpenBasket
functions.description:
### 	Loads and verifies a Basket record for the current shopping session

This function attempts to locate a Basket record for the session identified by g.Session_ID.
If a Basket record exists, it is checked for expiration and discarded if it has expired.

If a valid, unexpired Basket record is found, shopping session parameters are verified and the following
verification variables are set:

*	g.Customer_Session_Verified
* g.Affiliate_Session_Verified
* g.Checkout_Session_Verified

* __@param__ [out] basket A variable that will receive an existing, valid Basket record

\return		1 if the current session exists and has not expired, 0 if the session is new or has expired

* __@param__ [in] address The email address to be validated

\return	1 if the email address appears to be valid, 0 if it does not

functions.name: Phone_Validate
functions.description:
### Validates a phone number

For the US and Germany, the phone number must contain only digits and common delimiter characters.
For all countries, the phone number must be non-empty.

* __@param__ [in] phone The phone number to be validated
* __@param__ [in] country The 2-character alphanumeric country code in which the phone number is expected to reside

\return	1 if the phone number appears to be valid, 0 if it does not

functions.name: Zip_Validate
functions.description:
### 	Validates a zip or postal code

* For the US, zip must be a valid 5 digit or Zip+4 zip code
* For Germany, zip must be exactly 5 numeric digits
* For all other countries, zip must have a length greater than 0

* __@param__ [in] zip The zip/postal code to be validated
* __@param__ [in] country The 2-character alphanumeric country code in which the zip code is expected to reside

\return	1 if the zip code appears to be valid, 0 if it does not

functions.name: StandardFields_Validate_NonOptional_Address
functions.description:
### 	Performs validation of a non-optional shipping or billing address
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

This function validates a non-required address according to the passed in  fields variable, which is usually loaded from the StandardFields database for the current store.

 address contains the following members:
* fname
* lname
* email
* phone
* fax
* comp
* addr1
* addr2
* city
* state
* zip
* cntry

If one or more of the fields is invalid, a variable with the following name, prepended by  prefix is set to 1:
* [prefix]FirstName_Invalid
* [prefix]LastName_Invalid
* [prefix]Email_Invalid
* [prefix]Phone_Invalid
* [prefix]Fax_Invalid
* [prefix]Company_Invalid
* [prefix]Address1_Invalid
* [prefix]Address2_Invalid
* [prefix]City_Invalid
* [prefix]State_Invalid
* [prefix]Zip_Invalid
* [prefix]Country_Invalid

* __@param__ [in] fields The StandardFields record for the current store
* __@param__ [in] address The address to be validated
* __@param__ [in] prefix An optional prefix for setting of _Invalid variables

\return	1 if the address meets the requirements in fields, 0 if it does not

\sa StandardFields_Validate StandardFields_Load

functions.name: StandardFields_Validate
functions.description:
### 	Performs validation of both primary and secondary addresses
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

This function validates a set of primary and secondary addresses according to the passed in  fields variable, which is usually loaded from the StandardFields database for the current store.

 primary_address and  secondary_address contain the following members:
* fname
* lname
* email
* phone
* fax
* comp
* addr1
* addr2
* city
* state
* zip
* cntry

If one or more of the fields is invalid, a variable with the following name, prepended by  prefix is set to 1:
* [prefix]FirstName_Invalid
* [prefix]LastName_Invalid
* [prefix]Email_Invalid
* [prefix]Phone_Invalid
* [prefix]Fax_Invalid
* [prefix]Company_Invalid
* [prefix]Address1_Invalid
* [prefix]Address2_Invalid
* [prefix]City_Invalid
* [prefix]State_Invalid
* [prefix]Zip_Invalid
* [prefix]Country_Invalid

* __@param__ [in] fields The StandardFields record for the current store
* __@param__ [in] primary_setting * 'D' if the primary address is required * 'O' if the primary address is optional
* __@param__ [in] secondary_setting * 'D' if the secondary address is required * 'O' if the secondary address is optional * 'H' if the secondary address is hidden
* __@param__ [in] primary_address The primary address to be validated
* __@param__ [in] primary_prefix The prefix for the _Invalid variables for the primary address
* __@param__ [in] secondary_address The secondary address to be validated
* __@param__ [in] secondary_prefix The prefix for the _Invalid variables for the secondary address

\return	1 if the set of addresses meets the requirements in fields, 0 if it does not

\sa StandardFields_Validate_NonOptional_Address StandardFields_Load

functions.name: Adjusted_Price
functions.description:
### Adjusts a products price according to Price Groups

This function takes into account the price groups of a currently logged in shopping account as well as the price group overlap setting of the current store.

* __@param__ [in] product A product record, as loaded by one of the Runtime_Product... functions
* __@param__ [in] price The input price of the product
* __@param__ [in] cost The input cost of the product

\return	The sale price according to all price groups

\sa Adjusted_Price_LowLevel

functions.name: Adjusted_Price_LowLevel

* __@param__ [in] customer Customer record
* __@param__ [in] product Product record, as loaded by one of the Runtime_Product... functions
* __@param__ [in] price The input price of the product
* __@param__ [in] cost The input cost of the product

\return	The sale price according to all price groups

\sa Adjusted_Price

functions.name: Format_Address
functions.description:
### Arranges an address in a format suitable for display

The address is formatted into a multi-line format, using  seperator (sic) as the line delimiter.

* __@param__ [in] company Company
* __@param__ [in] name Name
* __@param__ [in] street Street address
* __@param__ [in] city City
* __@param__ [in] state State

functions.name: Validate_Attributes
functions.description:
### Validates a set of product attributes

In order to be valid, all required attributes must have values present, and all values must match an option in the database.

 attributes is an array of structures with the following members:
*  template_code	(optional) An attribute template code
*  code				Attribute code
*  value			Option or input field value

\deprecated	Modern callers should call Validate_Attributes_DetermineVariant() instead, which additionally returns a variant ID.

* __@param__ [in] product The product for which attributes are being validated
* __@param__ [in] prompt A boolean value indicating whether validation should automatically fail if the product has attributes
* __@param__ [in] attributes An array of currently selected attribute values
* __@param__ [in] attribute_count The count of items in  attributes
* __@param__ [out] basketoptions BasketOption records suitable for direct insertion into the database
* __@param__ [out] basketoption_count The count of items in  basketoptions

\return	1 if the attributes are valid, 0 otherwise.

\sa Validate_Attributes_DetermineVariant

functions.name: Validate_Attributes_DetermineVariant
functions.description:
### 	Validates a set of product attributes, returning a variant representing these attributes (if configured)
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

In order to be valid, all required attributes must have values present, and all values must match an option in the database.

 attributes is an array of structures with the following members:
*  template_code	(optional) An attribute template code
*  code				Attribute code
*  value			Option or input field value

* __@param__ [in] product The product for which attributes are being validated
* __@param__ [in] prompt A boolean value indicating whether validation should automatically fail if the product has attributes
* __@param__ [in] attributes An array of currently selected attributes, with each element containing the following members:
								*  code				Attribute code
								*  template_code	AttributeTemplateAttribute code (if  code refers to a "used" Attribute Template)
								*  value			Option code for multiple select attributes, any value for boolean attributes, or user-specified data for text or textarea attributes.
* __@param__ [in] attribute_count The count of items in  attributes
* __@param__ [out] basketoptions BasketOption records suitable for direct insertion into the database
* __@param__ [out] basketoption_count The count of items in  basketoptions
* __@param__ [out] variant_id The ID of a product variant matching this configured set of attributes, or 0

\return	1 if the attributes are valid, 0 otherwise.

If  unique_code is empty, an initial code is generated by extracting the first letter of each word in  name.
If  unique_code has a value, a series of random digits is appended.

* __@param__ [in] name An associated name or longer identifier that is a source for additional unique data
* __@param__ [in] unique_code A previous value if it was proven to be non-unique

\return	An item code

functions.name: QuickSortArray
functions.description:
### Sorts an array

The array is sorted using the Quick Sort algorithm.   subelement must contain a leading colon (:) if sorting an array of structures by a single member,
or may be empty if sorting an array of simple values.  Elements are compared using the MivaScript EQ operator.

* __@param__ [in,out] array The array to be sorted
* __@param__ [in] subelement The element within the array to be sorted
* __@param__ [in] direction * 1 to sort ascending * -1 to sort descending

functions.name: QuickSortArray_Sort
functions.description:
### Sorts an array using multiple comparisons to break ties

The array is sorted using the Quick Sort algorithm.

Each element in  comparisons contains the following members:
*  subelement The member to sort by, including the leading colon (:)
*  direction The direction in which to sort

Elements are compared using the MivaScript EQ operator according to each element in  comparisons.  If a comparison results in a tie, the next comparison is used.

* __@param__ [in,out] array The array to be sorted
* __@param__  left The index of the lowest element of the array to be sorted
* __@param__  right The index of the highest element of the array to be sorted
* __@param__  comparisons An array defining the comparisons to be used and the order in which they should be applied
* __@param__  comparison_count The number of elements in  comparisons

functions.name: ParseCookies
functions.description:
### 	Parses cookies sent by the browser and stores them in a structure
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

A member is created in  cookies with the name of the cookie equal to the member name, and the value of the member equal to the cookie's value.  This allows
cookies to be referenced directly by name.

* __@param__ [out] cookies A variable which will receive the cookies

functions.name: SetCookie
functions.description:
### 	Adds or updates a cookie in a cookie list
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

This function adds or updates a cookie in a cookie list, which may then be output in its entirety using OutputCookies().  In pr7-bugfix-2 and later,
all cookies are created with the HttpOnly attribute.

* __@param__ [in,out] cookies The cookie list to be updated
* __@param__ [in] name The name of the cookie to add or update
* __@param__ [in] value The value of the cookie
* __@param__ [in] domain The "domain" attribute of the cookie
* __@param__ [in] expires A time_t or RFC 1123 format date/time representing the expiration date of the cookie
* __@param__ [in] path The "path" attribute of the cookie
* __@param__ [in] secure A boolean value controlling the "secure" attribute of the cookie

\sa ParseCookies ClearCookie OutputCookies

functions.name: ClearCookie
functions.description:
### 	Marks a cookie in a cookie list for expungement
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

This function modifies a cookie list so that the specified cookie is explicitly cleared upon the next call to OutputCookies().  Clearing of the cookie
is accomplished by setting its expiration date to a time one year in the past.

* __@param__ [in,out] cookies The cookie list to be updated
* __@param__ [in] name The name of the cookie to clear
* __@param__ [in] domain The "domain" attribute of the cookie
* __@param__ [in] path The "path" attribute of the cookie
* __@param__ [in] secure A boolean value controlling the "secure" attribute of the cookie

\sa ParseCookies SetCookie OutputCookies

functions.name: OutputCookies
functions.description:
### 	Outputs a cookie list to the browser
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

* __@param__ [in] cookies The cookie list to be output

\return	1 on success, 0 on failure

functions.name: SelfReferentialURL
functions.description:
### 	Constructs a self-referential URL using s.documenturl and the HTTP Host header
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

This function examines s.documenturl to ensure that it matches the HTTP Host header sent by the client.  Depending
on the server configuration, this may or may not be the case.  If s.documenturl does not appear to be directly
self-referential, this function constructs a URL based on the HTTP Host header and remaining contents of s.documenturl.

The resulting URL will most likely work for the specific client that made the original request, but may not work for
other clients depending on their configuration.

functions.name: SelfReferentialURL_Failsafe
functions.description:
### 	Constructs a self-referential URL using s.documenturl and the HTTP Host header, using a fallback URL in certain cases
\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

* __@param__ [in] failsafe_url The URL to use if s.documenturl appears to be malformed

This function behaves identically to SelfReferentialURL(), except if the number of forward slashes in s.documenturl and the parameter failsafe_url
differ, s.documenturl is assumed to be malformed and failsafe_url is returned instead.

functions.name: CountOccurrences

\version	>= 5.60
\ingroup	PR7

* __@param__ [in] needle The string to search for
* __@param__ [in] haystack The string to search in

\return		The number of occurrences
